</tbody></table>
<h2>Opening Hours</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">Day</th><th style="padding:10px;">Hours</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Sunday – Thursday</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">8:00 AM – 8:00 PM</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;">Friday – Saturday</td><td style="padding:10px;">Closed to the public (hours vary for events)</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>Best Time to Visit</h2>
<div style="background:#f8fafc;border-radius:12px;padding:20px;margin:16px 0;">
<div style="margin-bottom:8px;"><span style="display:inline-block;width:140px;font-size:13px;">Morning</span><div style="display:inline-block;background:#22c55e;height:14px;border-radius:4px;width:30%;vertical-align:middle;"></div><span style="margin-left:8px;font-size:12px;color:#16a34a;">Quiet — Best for Studying</span></div>
<div><span style="display:inline-block;width:140px;font-size:13px;">Afternoon</span><div style="display:inline-block;background:#eab308;height:14px;border-radius:4px;width:55%;vertical-align:middle;"></div><span style="margin-left:8px;font-size:12px;color:#ca8a04;">Moderate — Students &amp; Researchers</span></div>
</div>
<h2>Tips</h2><ul><li>The exterior facade is one of the most photographed modern buildings in Riyadh, especially at sunset</li><li>Bring ID if you plan to access reading rooms or archives</li><li>Combine with a visit to nearby Kingdom Centre Tower for a fuller day in the Olaya district</li><li>Photography of the exterior is welcome; check current rules for photographing inside reading halls</li></ul>
<h2>How to Get There</h2><p>King Fahd National Library sits on King Fahd Road in the Olaya district. <strong>Airport Travel Taxis</strong> offers fixed-price transfers from the airport and all Riyadh hotels. <a href="/booking">Book your transfer</a></p>',
