(
  'Imam Turki Bin Abdullah Grand Mosque: Visitor Guide',
  'imam-turki-bin-abdullah-grand-mosque-visitor-guide',
  'Complete visitor guide to Imam Turki Bin Abdullah Grand Mosque in Riyadh — history, visiting etiquette, opening hours, and how to get there.',
  '<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1519817650390-64a93db51149?w=900&q=80" alt="Imam Turki Bin Abdullah Grand Mosque Riyadh" style="width:100%;border-radius:16px;margin-bottom:24px;max-height:400px;object-fit:cover;"/>
<h2>Imam Turki Bin Abdullah Grand Mosque: Visitor Guide</h2>
<p>Imam Turki Bin Abdullah Grand Mosque is one of Riyadh''s largest and most significant mosques, standing in the historic Qasr Al-Hukm district beside Al Masmak Fortress. Built in traditional Najdi style with a modern scale, it serves as a major congregational mosque for the old city and a striking example of contemporary Saudi religious architecture.</p>
<h2>Location &amp; Drive Times</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">From</th><th style="padding:10px;">Drive Time</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">King Khalid International Airport (RUH)</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:center;">~30 min</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Al Masmak Fortress</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:center;">~2 min</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;">Kingdom Centre Tower</td><td style="padding:10px;text-align:center;">~15 min</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>Visitor Information</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">Detail</th><th style="padding:10px;">Info</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Entry</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><strong>Free</strong></td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Dress Code</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Modest dress required; women should bring a headscarf</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;">Non-Muslim Visitors</td><td style="padding:10px;">Exterior viewing welcome; entry outside prayer times is generally respectful to arrange in advance</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>Opening Hours</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">Day</th><th style="padding:10px;">Hours</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Daily</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Open around the five daily prayer times</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;">Friday</td><td style="padding:10px;">Busiest — main congregational prayer</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>Best Time to Visit</h2>
<div style="background:#f8fafc;border-radius:12px;padding:20px;margin:16px 0;">
<div style="margin-bottom:8px;"><span style="display:inline-block;width:140px;font-size:13px;">Between Prayer Times</span><div style="display:inline-block;background:#22c55e;height:14px;border-radius:4px;width:25%;vertical-align:middle;"></div><span style="margin-left:8px;font-size:12px;color:#16a34a;">Quiet — Best for Viewing</span></div>
<div><span style="display:inline-block;width:140px;font-size:13px;">Friday Prayer</span><div style="display:inline-block;background:#ef4444;height:14px;border-radius:4px;width:95%;vertical-align:middle;"></div><span style="margin-left:8px;font-size:12px;color:#dc2626;">Very Busy</span></div>
</div>
<h2>Tips</h2><ul><li>Visit between prayer times for the calmest experience and best photography of the architecture</li><li>Pair with a walk through Al Masmak Fortress and the Qasr Al-Hukm district, both a short walk away</li><li>Dress modestly regardless of whether you plan to enter</li><li>Avoid visiting during Friday midday prayer unless attending, as the area gets very crowded</li></ul>
<h2>How to Get There</h2><p>Imam Turki Bin Abdullah Grand Mosque is located in the Qasr Al-Hukm district of Old Riyadh. <strong>Airport Travel Taxis</strong> offers fixed-price transfers from the airport and all Riyadh hotels. <a href="/booking">Book your transfer</a></p>',
