(
  'Heet Cave Riyadh: A Complete Travel Guide',
  'heet-cave-riyadh-complete-travel-guide',
  'Complete guide to Heet Cave near Riyadh — the underground pool, what to expect, safety tips, and how to get there.',
  '<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1516131206008-dd041a9764fd?w=900&q=80" alt="Heet Cave underground pool near Riyadh" style="width:100%;border-radius:16px;margin-bottom:24px;max-height:400px;object-fit:cover;"/>
<h2>Heet Cave Riyadh: A Complete Travel Guide</h2>
<p>Heet Cave, known locally as Kahf Heet, is a striking collapsed limestone sinkhole a couple of hours from Riyadh, with a deep underground pool at its base. It''s one of the region''s most memorable natural attractions, drawing hikers and adventure travellers for the descent and the eerie beauty of the cavern itself.</p>
<h2>Location &amp; Drive Times</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">From</th><th style="padding:10px;">Drive Time</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Central Riyadh</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:center;">~1.5–2 hours</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">King Khalid International Airport (RUH)</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:center;">~2 hours</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>What to Expect</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">Feature</th><th style="padding:10px;">Detail</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><strong>Descent</strong></td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Steep, rocky climb down into the sinkhole — moderate fitness required</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><strong>Underground Pool</strong></td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Deep, cold water at the base of the cave</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;"><strong>Guides</strong></td><td style="padding:10px;">Strongly recommended for first-time visitors</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>Visitor Information</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">Detail</th><th style="padding:10px;">Info</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Entry</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><strong>Free (guided tours charge separately)</strong></td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;">Recommended Gear</td><td style="padding:10px;">Sturdy hiking shoes, headlamp, swimwear if entering the pool</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>Best Time to Visit</h2>
<div style="background:#f8fafc;border-radius:12px;padding:20px;margin:16px 0;">
<div style="margin-bottom:8px;"><span style="display:inline-block;width:140px;font-size:13px;">Winter (Nov–Mar)</span><div style="display:inline-block;background:#22c55e;height:14px;border-radius:4px;width:90%;vertical-align:middle;"></div><span style="margin-left:8px;font-size:12px;color:#16a34a;">Best — Cooler for the Climb</span></div>
<div><span style="display:inline-block;width:140px;font-size:13px;">Summer (Jun–Aug)</span><div style="display:inline-block;background:#ef4444;height:14px;border-radius:4px;width:80%;vertical-align:middle;"></div><span style="margin-left:8px;font-size:12px;color:#dc2626;">Very Hot — Physically Demanding</span></div>
</div>
<h2>Tips</h2><ul><li>Go with an experienced local guide, especially if you plan to enter the water — depth and currents inside the cave can be misleading</li><li>Wear proper hiking shoes; the descent is uneven and can be slippery</li><li>Bring a headlamp or flashlight, as parts of the cave interior are dark even during the day</li><li>Visit in cooler months — the climb back up is demanding in summer heat</li></ul>
<h2>How to Get There</h2><p>Heet Cave is roughly a two-hour drive from central Riyadh, best visited with an organised tour or 4x4. <strong>Airport Travel Taxis</strong> can arrange transfers to nearby meeting points for guided excursions. <a href="/booking">Book your transfer</a></p>',
