(
  'Murabba Historical Palace: Everything You Need to Know',
  'murabba-historical-palace-everything-you-need-to-know',
  'Complete guide to Murabba Historical Palace in Riyadh — King Abdulaziz''s restored residence, exhibits, opening hours, and how to get there.',
  '<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1590867286331-1a25f9c650f4?w=900&q=80" alt="Murabba Historical Palace Riyadh Najdi architecture" style="width:100%;border-radius:16px;margin-bottom:24px;max-height:400px;object-fit:cover;"/>
<h2>Murabba Historical Palace: Everything You Need to Know</h2>
<p>Murabba Historical Palace was the residence of King Abdulaziz, founder of modern Saudi Arabia, and remains one of the best-preserved examples of traditional Najdi mud-brick architecture in Riyadh. Set within the King Abdulaziz Historical Center in Al Murabba district, it offers a direct link to the early days of the Saudi state.</p>
